<paragraph id="8B90152CEF67A2268BD5FBDEFC09F96A" blockId="16.[151,1437,726,2011]" pageId="16" pageNumber="317">
Male imago. Length (mm): body, 6.5–7.5; fore wing, 6.0–6.5; hind wing, 3.0–3.3; cerci, 18.0–21.5; fore leg, 2.8–3.4. General coloration whitish yellow (
<figureCitation id="131409A9EF67A226898DFBFAFC8EFBE2" box="[671,774,1086,1111]" captionStart="FIGURES 167 – 170" captionStartId="44.[151,264,1960,1983]" captionTargetBox="[257,1322,202,1910]" captionTargetId="figure@44.[246,1329,193,1922]" captionTargetPageId="44" captionText="FIGURES 167 – 170. Male imago, general view, dorsal: 167, C. dasilvai sp. nov.; 168, C. zunigae sp. nov.; 169, C. pereirae sp. nov.; 170, C. janae sp. nov." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/838480/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="317">Fig. 167</figureCitation>
). Head yellowish, completely shaded with gray dorsally except around median ocellus and base of antenna. Antennae yellowish white, shaded with gray. Thorax (
<figureCitation id="131409A9EF67A2268E3CFBA6FA18FBCE" box="[1326,1424,1122,1147]" captionStart="FIGURES 167 – 170" captionStartId="44.[151,264,1960,1983]" captionTargetBox="[257,1322,202,1910]" captionTargetId="figure@44.[246,1329,193,1922]" captionTargetPageId="44" captionText="FIGURES 167 – 170. Male imago, general view, dorsal: 167, C. dasilvai sp. nov.; 168, C. zunigae sp. nov.; 169, C. pereirae sp. nov.; 170, C. janae sp. nov." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/838480/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="317">Fig. 167</figureCitation>
). Pronotum hyaline translucent, very slightly shaded with light gray on lateral and hind margins; prosternum and propleura pale, with grayish spot between coxae. Mesonotum yellowish, shaded with gray very slightly on median zone of scutum but darker on and between 
<collectionCode id="ED3E8DE9EF67A226899AFB0BFD32FB52" box="[648,698,1231,1255]" country="USA" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15543" name="Parasitic Seed Plants" pageId="16" pageNumber="317">PSP</collectionCode>
; pleura and sterna yellowish white, without shading; metathorax yellowish, shaded with gray medially on notum. Legs. Fore leg whitish translucent, shaded completely with purplish gray except at base of tarsomeres and claws; middle and hind legs yellowish translucent. Wings. Membrane hyaline veins shaded slightly gray, paler toward apex, cross veins hyaline except slightly shaded gray on C area. Hind wing with faintly grayish veins, Sc darker. Abdomen whitish translucent, shaded slightly with gray on terga except on mediolongitudinal line, intersegmental membranes and pale lateromedian dash on terga III–VII, terga VIII–IX shaded more uniformly but with some pale spots, tergum X pale with light gray hind margin. Abdominal sterna translucent white, yellowish toward gill sclerites and sternum IX. Genitalia (
<figureCitation id="131409A9EF67A2268FDFFA0EFAD2FA56" box="[1229,1370,1482,1507]" captionStart="FIGURES 51 – 59" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1910,1933]" captionTargetBox="[172,1421,199,1890]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[172,1421,193,1890]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 51 – 59. male imagos. Campsurus cuyuniensis: 51, paratype forceps (CUIC 2434); 52, same but from another paratype; 53, male genitalia from French Guiana specimen (FAMU), v. v. Campsurus nessimiani sp. nov.: 54, genitalia, v. v.; 55, same, l. v. Campsurus dasilvai sp. nov.: 56, genitalia, v. v.; 57, same, l. v.; 58, genitalia, v. v. (SEM), with detail of microlepides on sternum IX; 59, details of penes, v. v. (SEM)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/838448/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="317">Figs. 56–59</figureCitation>
): pale except grayish secondary lobe of penes; sternum IX with truncate (
<figureCitation id="131409A9EF67A22688B9FA2AFB88F9B2" box="[939,1024,1518,1543]" captionStart="FIGURES 51 – 59" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1910,1933]" captionTargetBox="[172,1421,199,1890]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[172,1421,193,1890]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 51 – 59. male imagos. Campsurus cuyuniensis: 51, paratype forceps (CUIC 2434); 52, same but from another paratype; 53, male genitalia from French Guiana specimen (FAMU), v. v. Campsurus nessimiani sp. nov.: 54, genitalia, v. v.; 55, same, l. v. Campsurus dasilvai sp. nov.: 56, genitalia, v. v.; 57, same, l. v.; 58, genitalia, v. v. (SEM), with detail of microlepides on sternum IX; 59, details of penes, v. v. (SEM)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/838448/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="317">Fig. 56</figureCitation>
) to slightly concave (
<figureCitation id="131409A9EF67A2268E10FA2AFADFF9B2" box="[1282,1367,1518,1543]" captionStart="FIGURES 51 – 59" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1910,1933]" captionTargetBox="[172,1421,199,1890]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[172,1421,193,1890]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 51 – 59. male imagos. Campsurus cuyuniensis: 51, paratype forceps (CUIC 2434); 52, same but from another paratype; 53, male genitalia from French Guiana specimen (FAMU), v. v. Campsurus nessimiani sp. nov.: 54, genitalia, v. v.; 55, same, l. v. Campsurus dasilvai sp. nov.: 56, genitalia, v. v.; 57, same, l. v.; 58, genitalia, v. v. (SEM), with detail of microlepides on sternum IX; 59, details of penes, v. v. (SEM)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/838448/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="317">Fig. 58</figureCitation>
) hind margin, covered by 3–7 pointed microlepides (detail on 
<figureCitation id="131409A9EF67A226881CF9D6FCE9F99E" box="[782,865,1554,1579]" captionStart="FIGURES 51 – 59" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1910,1933]" captionTargetBox="[172,1421,199,1890]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[172,1421,193,1890]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 51 – 59. male imagos. Campsurus cuyuniensis: 51, paratype forceps (CUIC 2434); 52, same but from another paratype; 53, male genitalia from French Guiana specimen (FAMU), v. v. Campsurus nessimiani sp. nov.: 54, genitalia, v. v.; 55, same, l. v. Campsurus dasilvai sp. nov.: 56, genitalia, v. v.; 57, same, l. v.; 58, genitalia, v. v. (SEM), with detail of microlepides on sternum IX; 59, details of penes, v. v. (SEM)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/838448/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="317">Fig. 58</figureCitation>
); pedestal of each side touching basally, with large apically rounded parastylus (in ventral view, 
<figureCitation id="131409A9EF67A2268986F9F2FC93F9FA" box="[660,795,1590,1615]" captionStart="FIGURES 51 – 59" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1910,1933]" captionTargetBox="[172,1421,199,1890]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[172,1421,193,1890]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 51 – 59. male imagos. Campsurus cuyuniensis: 51, paratype forceps (CUIC 2434); 52, same but from another paratype; 53, male genitalia from French Guiana specimen (FAMU), v. v. Campsurus nessimiani sp. nov.: 54, genitalia, v. v.; 55, same, l. v. Campsurus dasilvai sp. nov.: 56, genitalia, v. v.; 57, same, l. v.; 58, genitalia, v. v. (SEM), with detail of microlepides on sternum IX; 59, details of penes, v. v. (SEM)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/838448/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="317">Figs. 56, 58</figureCitation>
) but acute at lateral view (arrow in 
<figureCitation id="131409A9EF67A2268FA3F9F2FA8CF9FA" box="[1201,1284,1590,1615]" captionStart="FIGURES 51 – 59" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1910,1933]" captionTargetBox="[172,1421,199,1890]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[172,1421,193,1890]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 51 – 59. male imagos. Campsurus cuyuniensis: 51, paratype forceps (CUIC 2434); 52, same but from another paratype; 53, male genitalia from French Guiana specimen (FAMU), v. v. Campsurus nessimiani sp. nov.: 54, genitalia, v. v.; 55, same, l. v. Campsurus dasilvai sp. nov.: 56, genitalia, v. v.; 57, same, l. v.; 58, genitalia, v. v. (SEM), with detail of microlepides on sternum IX; 59, details of penes, v. v. (SEM)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/838448/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="317">Fig. 57</figureCitation>
), round inner corner strongly projected (ic in 
<figureCitation id="131409A9EF67A2268916F99EFDD2F9C6" box="[516,602,1626,1651]" captionStart="FIGURES 51 – 59" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1910,1933]" captionTargetBox="[172,1421,199,1890]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[172,1421,193,1890]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 51 – 59. male imagos. Campsurus cuyuniensis: 51, paratype forceps (CUIC 2434); 52, same but from another paratype; 53, male genitalia from French Guiana specimen (FAMU), v. v. Campsurus nessimiani sp. nov.: 54, genitalia, v. v.; 55, same, l. v. Campsurus dasilvai sp. nov.: 56, genitalia, v. v.; 57, same, l. v.; 58, genitalia, v. v. (SEM), with detail of microlepides on sternum IX; 59, details of penes, v. v. (SEM)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/838448/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="317">Fig. 56</figureCitation>
); forceps whitish except grayish at base; base of penes wide proximally, narrowing abruptly on distal half (bp in 
<figureCitation id="131409A9EF67A2268973F9BAFD3EF922" box="[609,694,1662,1687]" captionStart="FIGURES 51 – 59" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1910,1933]" captionTargetBox="[172,1421,199,1890]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[172,1421,193,1890]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 51 – 59. male imagos. Campsurus cuyuniensis: 51, paratype forceps (CUIC 2434); 52, same but from another paratype; 53, male genitalia from French Guiana specimen (FAMU), v. v. Campsurus nessimiani sp. nov.: 54, genitalia, v. v.; 55, same, l. v. Campsurus dasilvai sp. nov.: 56, genitalia, v. v.; 57, same, l. v.; 58, genitalia, v. v. (SEM), with detail of microlepides on sternum IX; 59, details of penes, v. v. (SEM)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/838448/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="317">Fig. 56</figureCitation>
); main lobe of penes (ml in 
<figureCitation id="131409A9EF67A22688E8F9BAFBC4F922" box="[1018,1100,1662,1687]" captionStart="FIGURES 51 – 59" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1910,1933]" captionTargetBox="[172,1421,199,1890]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[172,1421,193,1890]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 51 – 59. male imagos. Campsurus cuyuniensis: 51, paratype forceps (CUIC 2434); 52, same but from another paratype; 53, male genitalia from French Guiana specimen (FAMU), v. v. Campsurus nessimiani sp. nov.: 54, genitalia, v. v.; 55, same, l. v. Campsurus dasilvai sp. nov.: 56, genitalia, v. v.; 57, same, l. v.; 58, genitalia, v. v. (SEM), with detail of microlepides on sternum IX; 59, details of penes, v. v. (SEM)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/838448/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="317">Fig. 56</figureCitation>
) very wide at base, large and sclerotized, slightly curved ventrally and with pointed apex; secondary membranous lobe of penes (sl in 
<figureCitation id="131409A9EF67A2268E50F966FA1CF90E" box="[1346,1428,1698,1723]" captionStart="FIGURES 51 – 59" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1910,1933]" captionTargetBox="[172,1421,199,1890]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[172,1421,193,1890]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 51 – 59. male imagos. Campsurus cuyuniensis: 51, paratype forceps (CUIC 2434); 52, same but from another paratype; 53, male genitalia from French Guiana specimen (FAMU), v. v. Campsurus nessimiani sp. nov.: 54, genitalia, v. v.; 55, same, l. v. Campsurus dasilvai sp. nov.: 56, genitalia, v. v.; 57, same, l. v.; 58, genitalia, v. v. (SEM), with detail of microlepides on sternum IX; 59, details of penes, v. v. (SEM)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/838448/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="317">Fig. 56</figureCitation>
) large and cylindrical. Caudal filament translucent yellowish white.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C33546A7EF67A2268BD5F92EFC69F893" pageId="16" pageNumber="317" type="etymology">
