<subSubSection id="C33546A7EF67A2278BD5F892FE24FEA9" lastPageId="17" lastPageNumber="318" pageId="16" pageNumber="317" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8B90152CEF67A2278BD5F892FE24FEA9" blockId="16.[151,1437,726,2011]" lastBlockId="17.[151,1436,151,357]" lastPageId="17" lastPageNumber="318" pageId="16" pageNumber="317">
<emphasis id="B95BC93EEF67A2268BD5F892FEC9F8DA" bold="true" box="[199,321,1878,1903]" pageId="16" pageNumber="317">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C2F6EAFEF67A2268A5BF893FDA1F8DA" authority="Molineri &amp; Salles, 2017" authorityName="Molineri &amp; Salles" authorityYear="2017" box="[329,553,1878,1903]" class="Insecta" family="Polymitarcyidae" genus="Campsurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="317" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dasilvai" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B95BC93EEF67A2268A5BF893FDA1F8DA" box="[329,553,1878,1903]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="317">Campsurus dasilvai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2687445EF67A2268922F892FD03F8DA" box="[560,651,1878,1903]" pageId="16" pageNumber="317" rank="species">
<emphasis id="B95BC93EEF67A2268922F892FD03F8DA" bold="true" box="[560,651,1878,1903]" pageId="16" pageNumber="317">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
is only known from male adults that can be characterized as follows: 1) posterior margin of male abdominal sternum IX truncate to slightly concave (
<figureCitation id="131409A9EF67A2268F00F8BEFB07F826" box="[1042,1167,1914,1939]" captionStart="FIGURES 51 – 59" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1910,1933]" captionTargetBox="[172,1421,199,1890]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[172,1421,193,1890]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 51 – 59. male imagos. Campsurus cuyuniensis: 51, paratype forceps (CUIC 2434); 52, same but from another paratype; 53, male genitalia from French Guiana specimen (FAMU), v. v. Campsurus nessimiani sp. nov.: 54, genitalia, v. v.; 55, same, l. v. Campsurus dasilvai sp. nov.: 56, genitalia, v. v.; 57, same, l. v.; 58, genitalia, v. v. (SEM), with detail of microlepides on sternum IX; 59, details of penes, v. v. (SEM)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/838448/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="317">Fig. 56, 58</figureCitation>
), sternum IX sculptured with 3 to 7 pointed microlepides (
<figureCitation id="131409A9EF67A226890EF85AFDF9F802" box="[540,625,1950,1975]" captionStart="FIGURES 51 – 59" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1910,1933]" captionTargetBox="[172,1421,199,1890]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[172,1421,193,1890]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 51 – 59. male imagos. Campsurus cuyuniensis: 51, paratype forceps (CUIC 2434); 52, same but from another paratype; 53, male genitalia from French Guiana specimen (FAMU), v. v. Campsurus nessimiani sp. nov.: 54, genitalia, v. v.; 55, same, l. v. Campsurus dasilvai sp. nov.: 56, genitalia, v. v.; 57, same, l. v.; 58, genitalia, v. v. (SEM), with detail of microlepides on sternum IX; 59, details of penes, v. v. (SEM)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/838448/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="317">Fig. 58</figureCitation>
); 2) pedestals long and slender, well-developed, outer-posterior margin projected and forming a long parastylus with rounded apex (truncate and apically pointed in lateral view, 
<figureCitation id="131409A9EF67A2268E2EF806FA07F86E" box="[1340,1423,1986,2011]" captionStart="FIGURES 51 – 59" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1910,1933]" captionTargetBox="[172,1421,199,1890]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[172,1421,193,1890]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 51 – 59. male imagos. Campsurus cuyuniensis: 51, paratype forceps (CUIC 2434); 52, same but from another paratype; 53, male genitalia from French Guiana specimen (FAMU), v. v. Campsurus nessimiani sp. nov.: 54, genitalia, v. v.; 55, same, l. v. Campsurus dasilvai sp. nov.: 56, genitalia, v. v.; 57, same, l. v.; 58, genitalia, v. v. (SEM), with detail of microlepides on sternum IX; 59, details of penes, v. v. (SEM)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/838448/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="317">Fig. 57</figureCitation>
), inner margin also projected but shorter (ic in 
<figureCitation id="131409A9EF66A227899FFF53FD57FF05" box="[653,735,151,176]" captionStart="FIGURES 51 – 59" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1910,1933]" captionTargetBox="[172,1421,199,1890]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[172,1421,193,1890]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 51 – 59. male imagos. Campsurus cuyuniensis: 51, paratype forceps (CUIC 2434); 52, same but from another paratype; 53, male genitalia from French Guiana specimen (FAMU), v. v. Campsurus nessimiani sp. nov.: 54, genitalia, v. v.; 55, same, l. v. Campsurus dasilvai sp. nov.: 56, genitalia, v. v.; 57, same, l. v.; 58, genitalia, v. v. (SEM), with detail of microlepides on sternum IX; 59, details of penes, v. v. (SEM)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/838448/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="318">Fig. 56</figureCitation>
); 3); penes separated and converging distally, each arm formed by a large dorsal sclerotized lobe with a wide base (ml in 
<figureCitation id="131409A9EF66A227883CFF78FCF3FF60" box="[814,891,188,213]" captionStart="FIGURES 51 – 59" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1910,1933]" captionTargetBox="[172,1421,199,1890]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[172,1421,193,1890]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 51 – 59. male imagos. Campsurus cuyuniensis: 51, paratype forceps (CUIC 2434); 52, same but from another paratype; 53, male genitalia from French Guiana specimen (FAMU), v. v. Campsurus nessimiani sp. nov.: 54, genitalia, v. v.; 55, same, l. v. Campsurus dasilvai sp. nov.: 56, genitalia, v. v.; 57, same, l. v.; 58, genitalia, v. v. (SEM), with detail of microlepides on sternum IX; 59, details of penes, v. v. (SEM)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/838448/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="318">Fig 56</figureCitation>
), and a relatively large ventral apically rounded membranous lobe (sl in 
<figureCitation id="131409A9EF66A2278AB7FF1BFE78FF4D" box="[421,496,223,248]" captionStart="FIGURES 51 – 59" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1910,1933]" captionTargetBox="[172,1421,199,1890]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[172,1421,193,1890]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 51 – 59. male imagos. Campsurus cuyuniensis: 51, paratype forceps (CUIC 2434); 52, same but from another paratype; 53, male genitalia from French Guiana specimen (FAMU), v. v. Campsurus nessimiani sp. nov.: 54, genitalia, v. v.; 55, same, l. v. Campsurus dasilvai sp. nov.: 56, genitalia, v. v.; 57, same, l. v.; 58, genitalia, v. v. (SEM), with detail of microlepides on sternum IX; 59, details of penes, v. v. (SEM)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/838448/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="318">Fig 56</figureCitation>
), apex of main lobe of penes acutely pointed (
<figureCitation id="131409A9EF66A22788E7FF1BFBC1FF4D" box="[1013,1097,223,248]" captionStart="FIGURES 51 – 59" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1910,1933]" captionTargetBox="[172,1421,199,1890]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[172,1421,193,1890]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 51 – 59. male imagos. Campsurus cuyuniensis: 51, paratype forceps (CUIC 2434); 52, same but from another paratype; 53, male genitalia from French Guiana specimen (FAMU), v. v. Campsurus nessimiani sp. nov.: 54, genitalia, v. v.; 55, same, l. v. Campsurus dasilvai sp. nov.: 56, genitalia, v. v.; 57, same, l. v.; 58, genitalia, v. v. (SEM), with detail of microlepides on sternum IX; 59, details of penes, v. v. (SEM)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/838448/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="318">Fig. 57</figureCitation>
); 4) small size (length of male fore wings 6.0– 
<quantity id="4CD7B8C9EF66A2278A55FEC0FE28FEA9" box="[327,416,260,285]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.5" pageId="17" pageNumber="318" unit="mm" value="6.5">6.5 mm</quantity>
).
</paragraph>
